27:01.723 --> 27:04.717
I'll need it to get the FT paper
in shape, anyway.

27:04.804 --> 27:06.759
Boston's yelling at me for it.

27:06.845 --> 27:10.757
Hello, Mary. Then I'll just need
your tissue rejection data.

27:10.844 --> 27:12.402
How's that coming along?

27:12.485 --> 27:16.442
Listen, how about I write the paper
one time and you collect the data?

27:16.525 --> 27:20.153
Sure. Just say when. Do you want
to see how it's shaping up?

27:20.245 --> 27:23.236
No, I trust you to make us look good.

27:29.645 --> 27:31.204
I'm exhausted.

27:31.285 --> 27:33.799
Too exhausted to see Claire tonight?

27:34.646 --> 27:36.600
No. Never.

27:37.605 --> 27:40.995
- You'll need these.
- What's that?

27:41.085 --> 27:43.235
Butazamine.

27:46.165 --> 27:49.920
She's heard that it makes sex
come on like Nagasaki.

27:50.005 --> 27:52.361
You're not feeding her pills, are you?

27:52.445 --> 27:54.402
Listen, baby brother,...

27:55.446 --> 27:59.485
..l've got her number.
This lady's hustling us for drugs.

28:01.205 --> 28:03.197
I don't think that's true at all.

28:03.286 --> 28:07.164
- I think we should drop her, Bev.
- You drop her!

28:14.966 --> 28:18.276
This is unknown territory
we're moving into.

28:20.166 --> 28:24.398
Just cos we're handcuffed together
doesn't mean I have to like you!

28:24.487 --> 28:25.919
Handcuffs?

28:26.006 --> 28:27.679
You don't get it, do you?

28:27.766 --> 28:29.325
Listen, honey-mud,...

28:29.407 --> 28:33.718
..we're on the run... and until we find
the release code to this thing...

28:33.808 --> 28:36.764
..we're gonna get to know
each other real well.

28:36.846 --> 28:39.760
I suggest we learn to like what we see.

28:41.848 --> 28:44.805
You're a very self-conscious reader.

28:46.167 --> 28:48.124
Just... Just loosen up...

28:48.208 --> 28:50.244
..and play.

28:50.328 --> 28:52.079
Come on.

28:54.288 --> 28:57.996
Didn't you ever do routines
as a kid? lmpersonations?

28:58.088 --> 29:01.558
The only impersonation I ever did
was my brother.

29:03.368 --> 29:06.121
I didn't know you had a brother.

29:08.088 --> 29:09.521
Yeah.

29:10.528 --> 29:12.280
We're not very close.

29:12.368 --> 29:15.281
Beverly... That's a woman's name.

29:16.648 --> 29:20.356
Why did your mom give you
a woman's name, I wonder?

29:20.448 --> 29:23.283
It's not a woman's name.
It's spelled differently.

29:23.369 --> 29:27.919
It's still a woman's name. Does your
brother have a woman's name, too?

29:28.009 --> 29:30.000
Merian... spelled with an E...

29:30.088 --> 29:31.681
..and an A.

29:31.770 --> 29:35.843
What are you trying to suggest?
That I'm gay or something?

29:35.929 --> 29:38.806
My mother wanted girls?

29:38.889 --> 29:42.599
What the fuck is this
bullshit psychoanalysis!

29:50.889 --> 29:53.608
Listen, Doctor,...

29:55.209 --> 29:58.360
..l think there's something
wrong with you.

29:59.009 --> 30:02.764
I don't know what it is,
I can't put a label on it, but...

30:03.810 --> 30:05.368
..you're subtly...

30:06.410 --> 30:08.162
..l don't know...

30:08.250 --> 30:10.081
..schizophrenic...

30:10.169 --> 30:12.126
..or something.

30:16.851 --> 30:19.319
Sometimes I like you very much...

30:20.130 --> 30:24.487
..and sometimes you're an amusing lay.
Not much more.

30:27.930 --> 30:29.887
And I can't figure out...

30:29.971 --> 30:31.722
..why.

30:47.650 --> 30:49.607
(whispers) Beverly.

30:53.691 --> 30:55.250
One for you.

30:58.011 --> 30:59.684
One for me.

31:11.572 --> 31:13.529
Please come this way.

31:21.572 --> 31:23.962
My dear...

31:26.692 --> 31:28.683
Sit down, have a drink,...

31:28.772 --> 31:30.729
..and tell me everything.

31:31.852 --> 31:33.809
I'm not sure I know everything.

31:33.893 --> 31:37.044
Start with all this
I've been hearing about you...

31:37.132 --> 31:39.806
..and the wonderful Mantle boys.

31:39.893 --> 31:41.644
What are you talking about?

31:43.093 --> 31:47.643
Claire, this is me - Laura.
Please don't be coy, it's tedious.

31:50.373 --> 31:52.330
Dear Beverly,...

31:52.413 --> 31:54.166
..dear Elliot.

31:54.253 --> 31:57.563
Some claim they can't
tell the difference,...

31:57.653 --> 32:01.249
..but not me, dear.
It's obvious to me that...

32:03.013 --> 32:07.405
Well, before I say anything gauche,
tell me which one you're seeing.

32:07.494 --> 32:09.690
You mean there's two of them?

32:09.774 --> 32:13.609
Don't be an ass, dear.
Of course there are two of them.

32:15.214 --> 32:17.171
They're twins, dear.

32:17.254 --> 32:20.008
Identical twins.

32:21.455 --> 32:24.207
My dear, you've gone absolutely pale.

32:25.815 --> 32:27.770
Have I said something?

32:27.854 --> 32:32.006
No, no, not at all.
Where's that waiter? I want some coffee.

32:33.374 --> 32:35.330
Oh, how sick-making.

32:36.934 --> 32:39.687
I have said something, haven't l?

32:39.774 --> 32:41.128
(thunder)

32:41.215 --> 32:44.174
You know,
I could get very fond of Butazamine.

32:44.255 --> 32:47.009
Ooooh...!

32:53.495 --> 32:55.052
Beverly,...

32:56.535 --> 33:00.608
..why haven't you told me that
your brother isn't just a brother?

33:00.697 --> 33:03.449
Ah, th... Ah, that.

33:03.536 --> 33:05.094
Yes, that.

33:06.136 --> 33:09.367
It never occurred to me.
I mean, he is just a brother.

33:09.456 --> 33:11.208
Um...

33:11.296 --> 33:13.857
- Is it important?
- Is it important?

33:14.896 --> 33:18.128
I've heard you live together
in the same apartment.

33:18.217 --> 33:19.967
Yeah, that's true.

33:21.096 --> 33:23.086
We both like ltalian furniture.

33:23.176 --> 33:25.531
God! Do you sleep in the same bed?

33:25.617 --> 33:27.413
Oh, Claire, come on!

33:27.496 --> 33:29.055
You come on!

33:29.136 --> 33:30.774
You told me...

33:30.857 --> 33:33.246
..you and your brother weren't close.

33:34.377 --> 33:39.326
And now I find out
not only are you identical twins,...

33:40.417 --> 33:42.372
..but you live together...

33:42.457 --> 33:44.413
..in the same apartment.

33:48.097 --> 33:49.849
What's he like,...

33:49.938 --> 33:51.576
..your twin?

33:56.937 --> 33:58.689
Well, I mean... er...

33:59.658 --> 34:01.808
Of course, h-he looks a lot like me.

34:03.058 --> 34:05.446
Are you identical psychologically?

34:05.538 --> 34:07.494
Um...

34:08.976 --> 34:11.047
No, I wouldn't say that.

34:12.418 --> 34:14.170
When can I meet him?

34:14.259 --> 34:16.215
You can't. I mean...

34:16.297 --> 34:18.255
..you don't want to.

34:20.739 --> 34:22.695
(thunder)

34:22.779 --> 34:25.737
But, Beverly... don't you understand?

34:29.257 --> 34:31.010
I have to meet him.

34:31.099 --> 34:32.248
Why?

34:32.339 --> 34:34.693
I want to know everything about you.

34:36.938 --> 34:38.896
I don't think it's a good idea.

34:38.978 --> 34:42.527
You don't want me to meet your twin.
Why is that?

34:42.619 --> 34:44.576
It's... It's difficult.

34:44.659 --> 34:46.217
It's very difficult.

34:46.299 --> 34:49.893
That's it, you see. I want to know
why it's difficult for you.

34:49.978 --> 34:53.255
- My button...
- It's important to me to know why.

35:02.340 --> 35:04.011
I suppose l...

35:04.101 --> 35:06.534
..l could arrange for you and...

35:06.620 --> 35:08.371
..Elliot...

35:09.780 --> 35:11.736
..to have a drink together.

35:11.820 --> 35:13.776
Uh-uh. Nix.

35:13.860 --> 35:15.657
No good.

35:15.740 --> 35:17.492
Why?

35:21.260 --> 35:23.854
I want to see you two together.

35:30.740 --> 35:33.699
I know he's going to have to in the end.

35:36.541 --> 35:38.497
- Ah, there you are.
- Here I am.

35:38.580 --> 35:41.221
I've been really looking forward to this.

35:41.301 --> 35:43.098
Well... er...

35:43.180 --> 35:44.933
Claire Niveau,...

35:45.021 --> 35:46.977
..this is my brother Elliot.

35:47.062 --> 35:51.373
Hi, Claire... I hope Bev's told you
what a big fan I am of your movies.

35:51.461 --> 35:55.420
No, he hasn't. As a matter of fact,
he hasn't mentioned you at all.

35:55.501 --> 35:57.857
Really? That's not very flattering.

35:59.222 --> 36:00.620
Well...

36:00.701 --> 36:02.454
Are you going to sit down?

36:02.541 --> 36:04.499
Yes, I am.

36:11.102 --> 36:15.220
I feel such a fool, actually.
I must be the only woman in town...

36:15.302 --> 36:18.612
..who doesn't know about
the fabulous Mantle twins.

36:19.662 --> 36:21.414
What are you drinking?

36:21.502 --> 36:26.896
Nothing. I want to be very sober right
at this moment. I want to be very clear.

36:33.703 --> 36:37.456
There really isn't any
telling you apart, is there?

36:37.544 --> 36:40.103
Absolutely identical in every respect.

36:40.262 --> 36:43.060
I'm actually a couple of millimetres taller.

36:45.624 --> 36:49.094
I bet somebody who knew you both -
how shall I put it? -

36:49.183 --> 36:52.334
..knew you both really well...

36:52.423 --> 36:54.379
..could tell the difference.

36:54.463 --> 36:57.899
Without measuring your height, I mean.

36:57.983 --> 36:59.736
What do you mean?

36:59.823 --> 37:04.022
Beverly's the sweet one,
and you're the shit. Am I right?

37:04.104 --> 37:08.620
This is some feisty lady
you've found, Beverly!

37:08.704 --> 37:13.732
Elliot, let's ease up on the bullshit for
a moment. You can be honest with me.

37:13.823 --> 37:16.384
After all, I am laying both of you, aren't l?

37:16.464 --> 37:17.942
Er, now, hang on a...

37:18.024 --> 37:20.413
It's a sweet little act you have.

37:20.505 --> 37:23.655
You soften them up
with all that smarmy concern...

37:23.744 --> 37:27.215
..and along comes Dracula here
and polishes them off.

37:30.464 --> 37:32.773
I was the one who fucked you first,...

37:32.864 --> 37:36.573
..but I gave you to my baby brother
because you weren't very good.

37:36.664 --> 37:38.814
Oh, God, no! Um... Claire,...

37:38.906 --> 37:40.656
..let me explain...

37:40.744 --> 37:42.974
You absolute shit!

37:43.065 --> 37:46.944
Explain what?! Explain... what?
Listen...

37:47.024 --> 37:52.622
I've been around a bit. I've seen some
creepy things in the movie business.

37:52.705 --> 37:55.981
This is the most disgusting thing
that's ever happened to me.

37:56.066 --> 37:58.863
- I doubt that.
- What is it with you, chum?

37:58.946 --> 38:02.494
You can't get it up
unless little brother's watching?

38:02.586 --> 38:04.542
I told you this was a bad idea.

38:06.505 --> 38:09.781
- Really stupid. I'm leaving.
- Don't bother.

38:19.067 --> 38:21.421
That solves that little problem.

38:23.025 --> 38:24.584
Jesus, Bev!

38:24.666 --> 38:26.225
Hey!

38:27.347 --> 38:30.702
- What's going on?
- I don't know, I'm... I'm... er...

38:30.786 --> 38:32.344
..a bit upset.

38:34.226 --> 38:37.424
Listen, I'll go and catch up with her.

38:37.506 --> 38:40.067
- I'll tell her it was all my fault.
- No!

38:42.708 --> 38:44.459
Leave her alone.

38:47.468 --> 38:49.776
I'll sort it out.

38:50.146 --> 38:53.663
I give you the winner
of the 1988 Feldman Award:

38:53.748 --> 38:56.306
Dr Elliot Mantle!

39:12.508 --> 39:15.818
I suppose all of us know
just how important it is...

39:15.908 --> 39:19.901
..for a practitioner to receive
the recognition of his peers.

39:21.068 --> 39:24.378
(Elliot) However,
I feel that this award tonight...

39:24.468 --> 39:26.822
..is not really for me,...

39:26.908 --> 39:30.025
..but rather for those women...

39:30.109 --> 39:33.384
..who have provided
that most precious thing:

39:33.469 --> 39:35.903
The gift of life.

39:44.629 --> 39:47.861
- I want to thank Dr Angus Lawson...
- Hi, how are you?

39:47.949 --> 39:51.339
..who gave me the time to pursue
my own research.

39:51.429 --> 39:55.661
But most of all
I want to thank my brother,...

39:55.748 --> 39:59.060
..my partner, Dr Beverly Mantle,...

39:59.149 --> 40:04.587
..who, true to form, is not here
wasting time basking in glory.

40:04.670 --> 40:06.706
Here, take mine.

40:06.789 --> 40:09.987
But is hard at work at the Mantle Clinic...

40:10.069 --> 40:12.025
Not true!

40:12.110 --> 40:14.464
Not true! I'm here!

40:20.310 --> 40:22.108
Oh, sorry.

40:25.990 --> 40:29.505
I see Beverly has been doing
a little basking, after all!

40:29.590 --> 40:31.343
He has a lot to celebrate.

40:31.431 --> 40:35.822
He has been recognised as one of
North America's leading clinicians.

40:35.911 --> 40:37.549
Ladies and gentlemen,...

40:37.630 --> 40:39.188
..Dr Beverly Mantle.

40:39.991 --> 40:42.631
- You all right?
- Had rather a lot to drink.

40:42.712 --> 40:44.667
Just want to say something.

40:44.751 --> 40:47.983
- I just want to say some...
- (microphone feedback)

40:48.992 --> 40:50.947
I just want to say something.

40:51.032 --> 40:52.988
(clears throat)

40:53.072 --> 40:56.507
There's been a fraud
perpetrated here tonight.

41:00.392 --> 41:02.542
The whole thing's a fraud!

41:05.911 --> 41:09.109
- He's Beverly and I'm Elliot!
- (laughter)

41:09.192 --> 41:11.581
- Just say thank you and get off.
- No!

41:11.672 --> 41:14.470
I want to say something else!

41:14.551 --> 41:16.986
A lot of you are probably wondering...

41:17.072 --> 41:19.028
..how we divide the work.

41:20.152 --> 41:22.108
Well, it's like this...

41:24.193 --> 41:26.945
I slave over the hot snatches...

41:27.032 --> 41:28.102
(gasps)

41:28.193 --> 41:31.582
..and Elliot... makes the speeches!

41:31.673 --> 41:33.106
For God's sake!

41:33.192 --> 41:38.220
I do everything for those bimbos, except
take them home and stick it in them!

41:38.312 --> 41:40.269
(audience gasps)

41:42.473 --> 41:46.864
Well, he's clearly been doing a lot
of celebrating. Who can blame him?

41:46.954 --> 41:48.909
Thank you so much. Thank you.

41:53.354 --> 41:55.309
(alarm clock beeping)

42:03.674 --> 42:05.630
(beeping grows louder)

42:07.594 --> 42:10.552
I'm sorry about the catastrophe
last night.

42:11.834 --> 42:15.986
It's true I had to smooth
a few ruffled feathers this morning.

42:16.074 --> 42:18.668
But now, baby brother,...

42:18.754 --> 42:20.312
..for the good news.

42:20.394 --> 42:21.827
Lawson has...

42:21.913 --> 42:26.227
..finally offered me the associate
professorship at the hospital.

42:26.314 --> 42:29.864
- One vodka martini, Doctor.
- Thank you, Sean.

42:30.634 --> 42:34.184
- Are you going to accept?
- Of course I'm going to accept.

42:34.275 --> 42:37.347
It's the next step to
chairman of the department.

42:37.434 --> 42:40.427
- What about the practice?
- It goes on as before.

42:40.514 --> 42:44.063
- Except you're not there.
- I won't be there as much, no.

42:48.234 --> 42:49.986
I'm not eating.

42:51.076 --> 42:53.430
- Are you all right?
- Yeah, I'm fine.

42:59.275 --> 43:00.755
What are those?

43:00.835 --> 43:02.791
Dex. I'm tired.

43:02.875 --> 43:05.788
- Want one?
- Er... no, thanks.

43:05.875 --> 43:08.833
If I can fly around, teach,
and do research,...

43:08.915 --> 43:12.067
..surely you can find time
for a few more patients?

43:12.156 --> 43:14.874
Sure. Why not?

43:49.517 --> 43:51.075
Good God!

43:52.117 --> 43:55.666
- I didn't know you were here.
- Shh, shh. Elly's asleep.

43:56.757 --> 43:58.713
His plane doesn't go till noon.

43:59.838 --> 44:02.477
I didn't realise you two were so friendly.

44:02.557 --> 44:04.514
We're not so friendly.

44:09.637 --> 44:11.390
You gonna take a shower?

44:12.478 --> 44:13.831
Um...

44:14.957 --> 44:16.789
No, l... er...

44:16.877 --> 44:18.675
You go ahead.

44:20.038 --> 44:21.596
OK.

44:21.677 --> 44:23.110
See ya.

44:28.839 --> 44:32.514
It seems so... cold and empty.

44:32.598 --> 44:37.195
You can call it empty,
or you can call it clean, sculptural.

44:37.279 --> 44:41.830
It's a question of the individual
nervous system, I think.

44:41.919 --> 44:44.797
That presupposes one has
an individual nervous system.

44:44.878 --> 44:46.197
Please?

44:58.319 --> 45:00.469
Er... thank you, I'll...

45:00.559 --> 45:02.312
I'll think about it.

45:14.999 --> 45:16.559
Claire...

45:16.640 --> 45:17.994
Yes?

45:23.199 --> 45:24.349
Oh,...

45:26.121 --> 45:27.678
..it's you.

45:31.721 --> 45:35.679
Or should I say, which one of you is it?

45:35.761 --> 45:37.911
Please, Claire, don't.

45:42.041 --> 45:44.349
Are you still doing the mini-series?

45:44.440 --> 45:47.911
Re-shoots. The director didn't
know what he was doing.

46:01.402 --> 46:02.834
Well,...

46:04.162 --> 46:06.117
..tell me how sorry you are.

46:07.882 --> 46:09.838
Tell me how much you miss me.

46:13.002 --> 46:15.994
My brother and I have always
shared everything.

46:16.082 --> 46:17.640
I'm not a thing.

46:17.721 --> 46:19.678
I mean people,...

46:19.761 --> 46:21.513
..experiences.

46:22.721 --> 46:24.871
It's never bothered me before now.

46:26.802 --> 46:28.758
It's different with me, is it?

46:29.922 --> 46:31.276
Yes.

46:31.362 --> 46:33.115
Yes, it is.

46:38.762 --> 46:40.718
Is Elliot jealous of me?

46:44.802 --> 46:47.442
Is he worried
I'll steal you away from him?

46:48.522 --> 46:51.879
No, he offered to come
and talk to you for me,...

46:51.963 --> 46:53.919
..to patch things up.

46:54.004 --> 46:55.959
That would've been amusing.

46:56.042 --> 46:57.716
Why didn't he?

46:58.723 --> 47:00.476
I wouldn't let him.

47:00.563 --> 47:04.351
Were you afraid I might like him
as much as I like you?

47:05.483 --> 47:07.439
Or maybe,...

47:08.924 --> 47:11.074
..when it came down to it,...

47:13.404 --> 47:15.554
..l couldn't see the difference.

47:15.643 --> 47:17.554
No!

47:17.644 --> 47:20.442
It doesn't work that way between us.

47:20.844 --> 47:22.800
I think it does.

47:23.604 --> 47:26.243
I think you two have
never come to terms...

47:26.324 --> 47:29.873
..with the way it really
does work between you.

47:39.564 --> 47:42.841
(whispers) No! Not while he's here.

47:45.284 --> 47:47.241
I don't want him to see us.

47:48.285 --> 47:50.037
All right,...

47:50.126 --> 47:52.685
..l'll just... separate you.

47:54.085 --> 47:55.643
Separate us?

47:55.725 --> 47:57.681
What do you mean?

48:09.845 --> 48:11.598
(Beverly screams)

48:12.885 --> 48:16.242
Ohh! Ohh! No! No! No! No!

48:21.165 --> 48:22.725
What happened?

48:22.806 --> 48:25.115
I'm sorry, I'm sorry, I was dreaming.

48:25.206 --> 48:26.958
- What about?
- About Elliot.

48:27.767 --> 48:30.201
- What happened?
- Oh, don't! Don't!

48:30.286 --> 48:32.437
Don't... touch it.

48:32.526 --> 48:34.279
Come to bed.

48:35.167 --> 48:36.725
Oh, Claire,...

48:36.806 --> 48:40.163
..l don't want to dream that again.
I can't!

48:45.046 --> 48:46.605
Take one of these.

48:46.688 --> 48:48.246
- What's that?
- Seconal.

48:48.328 --> 48:50.397
I guarantee you, you won't dream.

49:12.728 --> 49:15.083
Don't let me dream that again.

49:17.289 --> 49:21.441
The message that clearly emerges
from these complex encounters...

49:21.528 --> 49:23.644
..between physician and patient...

49:23.728 --> 49:26.844
..is that there is not only
a place in the clinic,...

49:26.928 --> 49:32.002
..but a demand for a philosophy.
A philosophy which mixes...

49:32.089 --> 49:36.878
..compassionate curiosity
with social responsibility.

49:39.208 --> 49:41.769
They'll discover they're gonna have to.

49:41.849 --> 49:43.201
(door buzzer)

49:43.288 --> 49:44.846
Yeah.

49:44.929 --> 49:48.968
Yeah. Look, David, I've got to go.
I've got company.

